\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. 
Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.  
\par  
\par PRIEST: }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6177181 READER: }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And the following Troparia:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE 1}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Having risen from sleep, we fall down before Thee, O Good One, and the angelical hymn we cry aloud to Thee, O Mighty One: Holy, holy, holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par From bed and sleep hast Thou raised me up, O Lord, enlighten my mind and heart, and open my  lips that I may hymn Thee, O Holy Trinity: Holy, holy, holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Now and ever and to the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Suddenly the Judge shall come, and the deeds of each will be laid bare; but with fear do we cry at midnight:  Holy, holy, holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (12 times)
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Prayer of St. Basil the Great to the Most Holy Trinity
\par 
\par As I rise from sleep, I thank Thee, O Holy Trinity, for through Thy great goodness and patience Thou wast not angered with me, an idler and sinner, nor hast Thou destroyed me with mine iniquities, but hast shown Thy usual love for mankin
d; and when I was prostrate in despair, Thou hast raised me up to keep the morning watch and glorify Thy power. And now enlighten my mind's eye, and open my mouth that I may meditate on Thy words, and understand Thy commandments, and do Thy will, and hymn
 Thee in heartfelt confession, and sing praises to Thine all-holy name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Another prayer:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par Glory to Thee, O King, Almighty God, Who through Thy divine and ma
n-loving providence hast vouchsafed me, a sinner and an unworthy one, to rise from sleep and obtain entry into Thy holy house. Receive, O Lord, the voice of my supplication even as Thou dost accept that of Thy holy and noetic hosts, and deign that through
 
my defiled lips, but from a pure heart and humble spirit, praise may be offered to Thee, so that I also, with the bright lamp of my soul, may become a companion of the wise virgins and glorify Thee, O God the Word, Who art glorified in the Father and the 
Spirit. Amen.
\par 
\par O come, let us worship God our King.
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and our God.
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Him, Christ Himself, our King and our God. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid4022315 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And three "reverences"}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid4022315 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\insrsid6177181 PSALM 50}{\insrsid6177181 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Have mercy on me, O God, according to Thy great mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression. Wash me thoroughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.
\par 
\par For I know mine iniquity, and my sin is ever before me. Against Thee only have I sinned and done this evil before Thee, that Thou mightest be justified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged. 
\par 
\par For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mother bear me. For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom hast Thou made manifest unto me. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow. 
\par 
\par Thou shalt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be humbled, they shall rejoice. 
\par 
\par Turn Thy face away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities. 
\par 
\par Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me. 
\par 
\par Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. 
\par 
\par Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Thy governing Spirit establish me. 
\par 
\par I shall teach transgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from bloodguiltiness. O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteousness. 
\par 
\par O Lord, Thou shalt open my lips, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise. 
\par 
\par For if Thou hadst desired sacrifice, I had given it; with wholeburnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased. 
\par 
\par A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise. 
\par 
\par Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. 
\par 
\par Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and wholeburnt offerings. 
\par 
\par Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4022315 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then, Prayer I, of St. Macarius the Great}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O God, cleanse me a sinner, for I have never done anything good in Thy sight; but deliver me from the evil one, and let Thy will be done in vi me, that I may open
 mine unworthy mouth without condemnation, and praise Thy holy name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer II, of the same saint:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Having risen from sleep, I offer unto Thee, O Saviour
, the midnight hymn, and falling down I cry unto Thee: Grant me not to fall asleep in the death of sin, but have compassion on me, O Thou Who wast voluntarily crucified, and hasten to raise me who am reclining in idleness, and save me in prayer and interc
ession; and after the night's sleep shine upon me a sinless day, O Christ God, and save me.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer III, of the same saint:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Having risen from sleep, I hasten to Thee, O Master, Lover of mankind, and by Thy loving-kindness, I strive to do Thy work, and I pr
ay to Thee: Help me at all times, in everything, and deliver me from every worldly, evil thing and every impulse of the devil, and save me, and lead me into Thine eternal kingdom. For Thou art my Creator, and the Giver, and Provider of everything good, an
d in Thee is all my hope, and unto Thee do I send up glory, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer IV, of the same saint:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O Lord, Who in Thine abundant goodness and Thy great compassion hast granted me, Thy servant, to go through the time o
f the night that is past without attack from any opposing evil: Do Thou Thyself, O Master, Creator of all things, vouchsafe me by Thy true light and with an enlightened heart to do Thy will, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4022315 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4022315 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer V, of St. Basil the Great:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O Lord Almighty, God of hosts and of all flesh, Who dwellest on high and lookest down on things that are lowly, Who searchest the heart and innermost being, and clearly foreknowest the secrets of men; O unoriginate and everlasting Light, 
with Whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning: 
\par 
\par Do Thou, O Immortal King, receive our supplications which we, daring because of the multitude of Thy compassions, offer Thee at the present time from defiled lips; and forgive us our sins, in deed,
 word, and thought, whether committed by us knowingly or in ignorance, and cleanse us from every defilement of flesh and spirit. 
\par 
\par And grant us to pass through the night of the whole pre
sent life with watchful heart and sober thought, ever expecting the coming of the bright and appointed day of Thine Only-begotten Son, our Lord and God and Saviour, Jesus Christ, whereon the judge of all shall come with glory to reward each according to h
is deeds. 
\par 
\par May we not be found fallen and idle, but watching, and upright in activity, ready to accompany Him into the joy and divine palace of His glory, where there is the ceaseless sound of those that keep festival, and the unspeakable delight of those 
that behold the ineffable beauty of Thy countenance. 
\par 
\par For Thou art the true Light that enlightenest and sanctifiest all, and all creation doth hymn Thee unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer VI, likewise by St. Basil:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par We bless Thee, O Most High God and Lo
rd of mercy, Who ever doest with us things both great and inscrutable, both glorious and awesome, of which there is no measure; Who grantest to us sleep for rest from our infirmities, and relaxation from the labors of our much toiling flesh. 
\par 
\par We thank Thee that Thou hast not destroyed us with our iniquities, but hast shown Thy loving-kindness to man as usual, and while we were lying in despair upon our beds, Thou hast raised us up that we might glorify Thy dominion. 
\par 
\par Wherefore, we implore Thy boundless go
odness: Enlighten the eyes of our understanding and raise up our mind from the heavy sleep of indolence; open our mouth and fill it with Thy praise, that we may be able steadily to hymn and confess Thee, Who art God glorified in all and by all, the unorig
inate Father, with Thine Only-begotten Son, and Thine All-holy and good and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer to the Most Holy Theotokos:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par I sing of thy grace, O Sovereign Lady, and I pray thee to grace my mind. 
\par 
\par Teach me to step aright in. the way of Christ's commandments. 
\par 
\par Strengthen me to keep awake in song, and drive away the sleep of despondency. 
\par 
\par O Bride of God, by thy prayers release me, bound with the bonds of sin.
\par 
\par Guard me by night and by day, and deliver me from foes that defeat me.
\par 
\par O bearer of God the Life-giver, enliven me who am deadened by passions.
\par 
\par O bearer of the unwaning Light, enlighten my blinded soul.
\par 
\par O marvelous palace of the Master, make me to be a house of the Divine Spirit.
\par 
\par O bearer of the Healer, heal the perennial passions of my soul.
\par 
\par Guide me to the path of repentance, for I am tossed in the storm of life.
\par 
\par Deliver me from eternal fire, and from evil worms, and from Tartarus.
\par 
\par Let me not be exposed to the rejoicing of demons, guilty as I am of many sins.
\par 
\par Renew me, grown old from senseless sins, O most immaculate one.
\par 
\par Present me untouched by all torments, and pray for me to the Master of all.
\par 
\par Vouchsafe me to find the joys of heaven with all the saints.
\par 
\par O most holy Virgin, hearken unto the voice of thine unprofitable servant.
\par 
\par Grant me torrents of tears, O most pure one, to cleanse my soul from impurity.
\par 
\par I offer the groans of my heart to thee unceasingly, strive for me, O Sovereign Lady.
\par 
\par Accept my service of supplication and offer it to compassionate God.
\par 
\par O thou who art above the angels, raise me above this world's confusion.
\par 
\par O Light bearing heavenly tabernacle, direct the grace of the Spirit in me.
\par 
\par I raise my hands and lips in thy praise, defiled as they are by impurity, O all immaculate one. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from soul corrupting evils, and fervently intercede with Christ, to Whom is due honor and worship, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer to our Lord Jesus Christ:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O my plenteously merciful and all merciful God, Lord Jesus Christ, through Thy great love Thou didst come down and become incarnate so that Thou mightest save all. 
\par 
\par And again, O Saviour, save me by Thy grace, I pray Thee. For if Thou shouldst save me for my works, this would not be grace or a gift, but rather a duty; yea, Thou Who art great in compassion and ineffable in mercy. 
\par 
\par For he that believeth in Me, Thou hast said, O my Christ, shall live and never see death. If, then, faith in Thee saveth the desperate, behold, I believe, save me, for Thou art my God and Creator. 
\par 
\par Let faith instead of works be imputed to me, O my God, for Thou wilt find no works which could justify me. But may my faith suffice instead of all works, may it answer for, may it acquit me, may it make me a partaker of Thine eternal glory. 
\par 
\par And let Satan not seize me and boast, O Word, that he hath torn me from Thy hand and fold. But whether I desire it or not, save me, O Christ my Saviour, forestall me quickly, quickly, for I perish. 
\par 
\par Thou art my God from my mother's womb. Vouchsafe me, O Lord, to love Thee now as fervently as I once loved sin itself, and also to work for Thee without idleness, diligently, as I worked before for deceptive Satan. 
\par 
\par But supremely shall I work for Thee, my Lord and God, Jesus Christ, all the days of my life, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer IX, to the Holy Guardian Angel:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O holy angel that standeth by my wretched soul and my passionate life, forsake not me a sinner, nor shrink from me because of mine intemperance. 
\par Give no place for the cunning demon to master me through the violence of my mortal body, strengthen my poor and feeble hand, and guide me in the way of salvation. 
\par 
\par Yea, O holy angel of Go
d, guardian and protector of my wretched soul and body, forgive me all wherein I have offended thee all the days of my life; and if I have sinned during the past night, protect me during the present day, and guard me from every temptation of the enemy, th
at I may not anger God by any sin. 
\par 
\par And pray to the Lord for me, that He may establish me in His fear, and show me, His servant, to be worthy of His goodness. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prayer X, to the Most Holy Theotokos:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par O my most holy lady Theotokos, through thy holy and all-powerful prayers, banish from me, thy lowly and wretched servant, despondency, forgetfulness, folly, carelessness, }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
(some will insert here specific sins and passions which afflict them)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  and all filthy,
 evil, and blasphemous thoughts from my wretched heart and my darkened mind. And quench the flame of my passions, for I am poor and wretched, and deliver me from many and cruel memories and deeds, and free me from all their evil effects. For blessed art t
hou by all generations, and glorified is thy most honourable name unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then, on a weekday, the Seventeenth Kathisma, on Saturday, the Ninth Kathisma}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par  
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4022315 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s37\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 
\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid148921 
\par }{\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 Seventeenth Kathisma}{\insrsid148921  
\par }\pard \s37\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\insrsid148921 Psalm}{\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395  118
\par }\pard \s37\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\b0\i0\cf0\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 
\par Blessed are the blameless in the way, who walk in the law of the Lord.
\par 
\par Blessed are they that search out His testimonies; with their whole heart shall they seek after Him.
\par 
\par For they that work iniquity have not walked in His ways.
\par 
\par Thou hast enjoined Thy commandments, that we should keep them most diligently.
\par 
\par Would that my ways were directed to keep Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Then shall I not be ashamed, when I look on all Thy commandments.
\par 
\par I will confess Thee with uprightness of heart, when I have learned the judgements of Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par I will keep thy statutes; do not utterly forsake me.
\par 
\par Wherewithal shall a young man correct his way? By keeping Thy words.
\par 
\par With my whole heart have I sought after Thee, cast me not away from Thy commandments.
\par 
\par In my heart have I hid Thy sayings that I might not sin against Thee.
\par 
\par Blessed art Thou, O Lord, teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par With my lips have I declared all the judgements of Thy mouth.
\par 
\par In the way of Thy testimonies have I found delight, as much as in all riches.
\par 
\par On Thy commandments will I ponder, and I will understand Thy ways.
\par 
\par On Thy statutes will I meditate; I will not forget Thy words.
\par 
\par Give reward unto Thy servant, quicken me and I will keep Thy words.
\par 
\par O unveil mine eyes, and I shall perceive wondrous things out of Thy law.
\par 
\par I am a sojourner on the earth, hide not from me Thy commandments.
\par 
\par My soul hath longed to desire Thy judgements at all times.
\par 
\par Thou hast rebuked the proud; cursed are they that decline from Thy commandments.
\par 
\par Remove from me reproach and contempt, for after Thy testimonies have I sought.
\par 
\par For princes sat and they spake against me, but Thy servant pondered on Thy statutes.
\par 
\par For Thy testimonies are my meditation, and Thy statutes are my counselors.
\par 
\par My soul hath cleaved unto the earth; quicken me according to Thy word.
\par 
\par My ways have I declared, and Thou hast heard me; teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Make me to understand the way of Thy statutes, and I will ponder on Thy wondrous works.
\par 
\par My soul hath slumbered from despondency, strengthen me with Thy words.
\par 
\par Remove from me the way of unrighteousness, and with Thy law have mercy on me.
\par 
\par I have chosen the way of truth, and Thy judgements have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par I have cleaved to Thy testimonies, O Lord; put me not to shame.
\par 
\par The way of Thy commandments have I run, when Thou didst enlarge my heart.
\par 
\par Set before me for a law, O Lord, the way of Thy statutes, and I will seek after it continually.
\par 
\par Give me understanding, and I will search out Thy law, and I will keep it with my whole heart.
\par 
\par Guide me in the path of Thy commandments, for I have desired it.
\par 
\par Incline my heart unto Thy testimonies and not unto covetousness.
\par 
\par Turn away mine eyes that I may not see vanity, quicken Thou me in Thy way.
\par 
\par Establish for Thy servant Thine oracle unto fear of Thee.
\par 
\par Remove my reproach which I have feared, for Thy judgements are good.
\par 
\par Behold, I have longed after Thy commandments; in Thy righteousness quicken me.
\par 
\par Let Thy mercy come also upon me, O Lord, even Thy salvation according to Thy word.
\par 
\par So shall I give an answer to them that reproach me, for I have hoped in Thy words.
\par 
\par And take not utterly out of my mouth the word of truth, for in Thy judgements have I hoped.
\par 
\par So shall I keep Thy law continually, for ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par 
\par And I walked in spaciousness, for after Thy commandments have I sought.
\par 
\par And I spake of Thy testimonies before kings, and I was not ashamed.
\par 
\par And I meditated on Thy commandments which I have greatly loved.
\par 
\par And I lifted up my hands to Thy commandments which I have loved, and I pondered on Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Remember Thy words to Thy servant, wherein Thou hast made me to hope.
\par 
\par This hath comforted me in my humiliation, for Thine oracle hath quickened me.
\par 
\par The proud have transgressed exceedingly, but from Thy law have I not declined.
\par 
\par I remembered Thy judgements of old, O Lord, and was comforted.
\par 
\par Despondency took hold upon me because of the sinners who forsake Thy law.
\par 
\par Thy statutes were my songs in the place of my sojourning.
\par 
\par I remembered Thy name in the night, O Lord, and I kept Thy law.
\par 
\par This hath happened unto me because I sought after Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Thou art my portion, O Lord; I said that I would keep Thy law.
\par 
\par I entreated Thy countenance with my whole heart: Have mercy on me according to Thy word.
\par 
\par I have thought on Thy ways, and I have turned my feet back to Thy testimonies.
\par 
\par I made ready, and I was not troubled, that I might keep Thy commandments.
\par 
\par The cords of sinners have entangled me, but Thy law have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par At midnight I arose to give thanks unto Thee for the judgements of Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par I am a partaker with all them that fear Thee, and with them that keep Thy commandments.
\par 
\par The earth, O Lord, is full of Thy mercy; teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Thou hast dealt graciously with Thy servant, O Lord, according to Thy word.
\par 
\par Goodness and discipline and knowledge teach Thou me, for in Thy commandments have I believed.
\par 
\par Before I was humbled, I transgressed; therefore Thy saying have I kept.
\par 
\par Thou art good, O Lord, and in Thy goodness teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Multiplied against me hath been the unrighteousness of the proud; but as for me, with my whole heart will I search out Thy commandments.
\par 
\par Curdled like milk is their heart; but as for me, in Thy law have I meditated.
\par 
\par It is good for me that Thou hast humbled me, that I might learn Thy statutes.
\par 
\par The law of Thy mouth is better to me than thousands of gold and silver.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God.}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  }{
\cs38\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 (Thrice)}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  
\par }{\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Lord, have mercy.}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  }{\cs38\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 (Thrice)}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  
