\par }\pard \s37\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\b0\i0\cf0\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 
\par Thy hands have made me and fashioned me; give me understanding and I will learn Thy commandments.
\par 
\par They that fear Thee shall see me and be glad, for on Thy words have I set my hope.
\par 
\par I have known, O Lord, that Thy judgements are righteousness, and with truth hast Thou humbled me.
\par 
\par Let now Thy mercy be my comfort, according to Thy saying unto Thy servant.
\par 
\par Let Thy compassions come upon me and I shall live, for Thy law is my meditation.
\par 
\par Let the proud be put to shame, for unjustly have they transgressed against me; but as for me, I will ponder on Thy commandments.
\par 
\par Let those that fear Thee return unto me, and those that know Thy testimonies.
\par 
\par Let my heart be blameless in Thy statutes, that I may not be put to shame.
\par 
\par My soul fainteth for Thy salvation; on Thy words have I set my hope.
\par 
\par Mine eyes are grown dim with waiting for Thine oracle; they say: When wilt Thou comfort me? For I am become like a wine-skin in the frost; yet Thy statutes have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par How many are the days of Thy servant? When wilt Thou execute judgement for me on them that persecute me? Transgressors have told me fables, but they are not like Thy law, O Lord.
\par 
\par All Thy commandments are truth.
\par 
\par Without a cause have men persecuted me; do Thou help me.
\par 
\par They well nigh made an end of me on the earth; but as for me, I forsook not Thy commandments.
\par 
\par According to Thy mercy quicken me, and I will keep the testimonies of Thy mouth.
\par 
\par For ever, O Lord, Thy word abideth in heaven.
\par 
\par Unto generation and generation is Thy truth; Thou hast laid the foundation of the earth, and it abideth.
\par 
\par By Thine ordinance doth the day abide, for all things are Thy servants.
\par 
\par If Thy law had not been my meditation, then should I have perished in my humiliation.
\par 
\par I will never forget Thy statutes, for in them hast Thou quickened me.
\par 
\par 
\par Middle
\par I am Thine, save me; for after Thy statutes have I sought.
\par 
\par Sinners have waited for me to destroy me; but Thy testimonies have I understood.
\par 
\par Of all perfection have I seen the outcome; exceeding spacious is Thy commandment.
\par 
\par O how I have loved Thy law, O Lord! the whole day long it is my meditation.
\par 
\par Above mine enemies hast Thou made me wise in Thy commandment, for it is mine for ever.
\par 
\par Above all that teach me have I gained understanding, for Thy testimonies are my meditation.
\par 
\par Above mine elders have I received understanding, for after Thy commandments have I sought.
\par 
\par From every way that is evil have I restrained my feet that I might keep Thy words.
\par 
\par From Thy judgements have I not declined, for Thou hast set a law for me.
\par 
\par How sweet to my palate are Thy sayings! more sweet than honey to my mouth.
\par 
\par From Thy commandments have I gained understanding; therefore have I hated every way of unrighteousness.
\par 
\par Thy law is a lamp unto my feet and a light unto my paths.
\par 
\par I have sworn and resolved that I will keep the judgements of Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par I was humbled exceedingly; O Lord, quicken me according to Thy word.
\par 
\par The free-will offerings of my mouth be Thou now pleased to receive, O Lord, and teach me Thy judgements.
\par 
\par My soul is in Thy hands continually, and Thy law have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par Sinners have set a snare for me, yet from Thy commandment have I not strayed.
\par 
\par I have inherited Thy testimonies for ever, for they are the rejoicing of my heart.
\par 
\par I have inclined my heart to perform Thy statutes for ever for a recompense.
\par 
\par Transgressors have I hated, but Thy law have I loved.
\par 
\par My helper and my protector art Thou; on Thy words have I set my hope.
\par 
\par Depart from me, ye evil-doers, and I will search out the commandments of my God.
\par 
\par Uphold me according to Thy saying and quicken me, and turn me not away in shame from mine expectation.
\par 
\par Help me, and I shall be saved; and I will meditate on Thy statutes continually.
\par 
\par Thou hast set at nought all that depart from Thy statutes, for unrighteous is their inward thought.
\par 
\par I have reckoned as transgressors all the sinners of the earth, therefore have I loved Thy testimonies.
\par 
\par Nail down my flesh with the fear of Thee, for of Thy judgements am I afraid.
\par 
\par I have wrought judgement and righteousness; O give me not up to them that wrong me.
\par 
\par Receive Thy servant unto good, let not the proud falsely accuse me.
\par 
\par Mine eyes have failed with waiting for Thy salvation, and for the word of Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par Deal with Thy servant according to Thy mercy, and teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par I am Thy servant; give me understanding, and I shall know Thy testimonies.
\par 
\par It is time for the Lord to act; for they have dispersed Thy law.
\par 
\par Therefore have I loved Thy commandments more than gold and topaz.
\par 
\par Therefore I directed myself according to all Thy commandments; every way that is unrighteous have I hated.
\par 
\par Wonderful are Thy testimonies; therefore hath my soul searched them out.
\par 
\par The unfolding of Thy words will give light and understanding unto babes.
\par 
\par I opened my mouth and drew in my breath, for I longed for Thy commandments.
\par 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God.}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  }{
\cs38\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 (Thrice)}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  
\par }{\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Lord, have mercy.}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  }{\cs38\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 (Thrice)}{\cs39\b\fs36\insrsid148921  
\par }{\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s37\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\i0\cf0\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 
\par 
\par }\pard \s37\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 Stasis 3 
\par }\pard \s37\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\b0\i0\cf0\insrsid148921\charrsid9002395 
\par Look upon me and have mercy on me, according to the judgement of them that love Thy name.
\par 
\par My steps do Thou direct according to Thy saying, and let no iniquity have dominion over me.
\par 
\par Deliver me from the false accusation of men, and I will keep Thy commandments.
\par 
\par Make Thy face to shine upon Thy servant, and teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Mine eyes have poured forth streams of waters, because I kept not Thy law.
\par 
\par Righteous art Thou, O Lord, and upright are Thy judgements.
\par 
\par Thou hast ordained as Thy testimonies exceeding righteousness and truth.
\par 
\par My zeal for Thee hath made me to pine away, because mine enemies have forgotten Thy words.
\par 
\par Thine oracle is tried with fire to the uttermost, and Thy servant hath loved it.
\par 
\par I am young and accounted as nothing, yet Thy statutes have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and Thy law is truth.
\par 
\par Tribulations and necessities have found me, Thy commandments are my meditation.
\par 
\par Thy testimonies are righteousness for ever; give me understanding and I shall live.
\par 
\par I have cried with my whole heart; hear me, O Lord, and I will seek after Thy statutes.
\par 
\par I have cried unto Thee; save me, and I will keep Thy testimonies.
\par 
\par I arose in the dead of night and I cried; on Thy words have I set my hope.
\par 
\par Mine eyes woke before the morning that I might meditate on Thy sayings.
\par 
\par Hear my voice, O Lord, according to Thy mercy; according to Thy judgement, quicken me.
\par 
\par They have drawn nigh that lawlessly persecute me, but from Thy law are they far removed.
\par 
\par Near art Thou, O Lord, and all Thy ways are truth.
\par 
\par From the beginning I have known from Thy testimonies that Thou hast founded them for ever.
\par 
\par Behold my humiliation and rescue me, for Thy law have I not forgotten.
\par 
\par Judge my cause and redeem me; for Thy word's sake quicken me.
\par 
\par Far from sinners is salvation, for they have not sought after Thy statutes.
\par 
\par Thy compassions are many, O Lord; according to Thy judgement quicken me.
\par 
\par Many are they that persecute me and afflict me; from Thy testimonies have I not declined.
\par 
\par I beheld men acting foolishly and I pined away, because they kept not Thy sayings.
\par 
\par Behold, how I have loved Thy commandments; O Lord, in Thy mercy, quicken me.
\par 
\par The beginning of Thy words is truth, and all the judgements of Thy righteousness endure for ever.
\par 
\par Princes have persecuted me without a cause, and because of Thy words my heart hath been afraid.
\par 
\par I will rejoice in Thy sayings as one that findeth great spoil.
\par 
\par Unrighteousness have I hated and abhorred, but Thy law have I loved.
\par 
\par Seven times a day have I praised Thee for the judgements of Thy righteousness.
\par 
\par Much peace have they that love Thy law, and for them there is no stumbling-block.
\par 
\par I awaited Thy salvation, O Lord, and Thy commandments have I loved.
\par 
\par My soul hath kept Thy testimonies and hath loved them exceedingly.
\par 
\par I have kept Thy commandments and Thy testimonies, for all my ways are before Thee, O Lord.
\par 
\par Let my supplication draw nigh before Thee, O Lord; according to Thine oracle give me understanding.
\par 
\par Let my petition come before Thee, O Lord; according to Thine oracle deliver me.
\par 
\par My lips shall pour forth a hymn when Thou hast taught me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par My tongue shall speak of Thy sayings, for all Thy commandments are righteousness.
\par 
\par Let Thy hand be for saving me, for I have chosen Thy commandments.
\par 
\par I have longed for Thy salvation, O Lord, and Thy law is my meditation.
\par 
\par My soul shall live and shall praise Thee, and Thy judgements will help me.
\par 
\par I have gone astray like a sheep that is lost; O seek Thy servant, for I have not forgotten Thy commandments.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs40\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 Glory to 
the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid4022315 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid148921 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 After the Kathisma, the Symbol of Faith (Page 24)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid148921 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid148921 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid4022315 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 After the Kathisma, the Symbol of Faith:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and earth, and of all things visible and invisible. 
\par 
\par And in one Lord Jesus Christ. the Son of God, the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages. Light of Light; true God of true God, begotten, not made; of one essence wit
h the Father by Whom all things were made; Who for us men, and for our salvation, came down from the heavens,  and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was crucified for us under Pontius Pilate, and suffered, and was b
uried; And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father. And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the living and the dead; Whose kingdom shall have no end. 

\par 
\par And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of Life; Who proceedeth from the Father; Who with the Father and the Son together is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. 
\par 
\par In One, Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Church. I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come. Amen.
\par 
\par Then:
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us}{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 . (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy K
ingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one. Amen. 
\par  
\par PRIEST:  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6177181 READER: }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Amen. 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par And these Troparia: 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 If it Be a Weekday:
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE EIGHT}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Behold, the Bridegroom cometh
 at midnight, and blessed is that servant whom He shall find watching, but unworthy is he whom He shall find heedless. Beware, therefore, O my soul, lest thou be weighed down with sleep; lest thou be given up to death, and be shut out from the kingdom. Bu
t rouse thyself and cry: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos have mercy on us.   
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Meditating on that terrible day, O my soul, watch, keeping thy lamp alight and filled with o
il; for thou knowest not when unto thee shall come the voice, saying: Behold the Bridegroom! Beware, therefore, my soul, lest thou fall into  slumber and be left outside, knocking, as were the five virgins; but wakefully watch, that thou mayest come to me
et Chris with good oil, and He shall bestow upon thee the divine chamber of His glory. 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Theotokion. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Thee, the unassailable wall, confirmation of salvation, O Virgin Theotokos do we supplicate, to destr
oy the counsels of the enemies, to change the sorrows of thy people into joy, to protect thy city, to ensure victory for pious, and to pray for the peace of the world; for thou, O Theotokos, art our hope}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 .
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 If it Be Saturday:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par \tab 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE TWO}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 O Thou Who art by nature uncreated, the Fashioner of all, do Thou open our lips that we may proclaim Thy praise while we cry: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181    
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par Imitating on earth the Hosts on high, we offer Thee, O Good One, the triumphant song: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 From bed and sleep hast Thou raised me up, O Lord; enlighten my mind and heart, and open my lips that I may hymn Thee, O Holy Trinity: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181     
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Lord, have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Forty times.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And this Prayer of the Hours:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Thou Who at a
ll times and every hour, in heaven and in earth, art worshipped and glorified, O Christ God, Who art long-suffering, plenteous in mercy, most compassionate, Who loveth the righteous and hast mercy on sinners, Who callest all to salvation through the promi
s
e of good things to come: Receive, O Lord, our prayers at this hour, and guide our life toward Thy commandments. Sanctify our souls, make chaste our bodies, correct our thoughts, purify our intentions, and deliver us from every sorrow, evil and pain. Comp
ass us about with Thy holy angels, that, guarded and guided by their array, we may attain to the unity of the faith and the knowledge of Thine unapproachable glory; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Thrice
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim, who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify.
\par 
\par In the name of the Lord, father }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Master) }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 bless. 
\par 
\par PRIEST: }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 God be gracious unto us and bless us, and cause Thy face to shine upon us, and have mercy on us. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6177181 READER: }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Amen 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 If it be a weekday service:
\par And if be Great Lent, or the first day of the Apostles fast, or the first day of the Nativity Fast (if it fall on a weekday), we say prayer of St. Ephraim the Syrian, dividing it into three parts and making three prostrations.
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 O Lord and  Master of my life, a spirit of idleness, despondency, ambition, talking give me not.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow up me Thy servant}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 . }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181     
\par 
\par }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Yea, O Lord and King, grant me to see my failings and not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then twelve "reverences" (bows from the waist with the sign of the Cross).}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 With each one we say: O God, cleanse me a sinner..  And then the entire prayer:}{
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
O Lord and Master of my life, a spirit  idleness, despondency, ambition, idle talking give me not. But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow on me Thy servant. Yea, O Lord and King, grant me to see my failings and
 not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then this  prayer:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par O Sovereign God, the Father Almighty, O Lord, the Only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ and Thou O Holy Spirit, one Godhead, one Power: Have mercy on me a si
nner, and by the judgments which Thou knowest, save me, Thine unworthy servant; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 If it be a Saturday Service this prayer of St. Eustratius:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Most highly do I magnify Thee, O Lord, for Thou didst take notic
e of my lowliness and hast not delivered me into the hands of mine enemies, but relieved my soul from wants. And now, O Master, let Thy hand shelter me and let Thy mercy descend upon me, for my soul is distracted and pained its departure from this my wret
c
hed and filthy  body, lest the evil of the adversary overtake it and make it stumble into the darkness for the  unknown and known sins amassed by me in this life. Be merciful unto me, O Master, and let not my soul see the dark  countenances of evil spirit
s
, but let it be received by angels  bright and shining. Glorify Thy holy name and by Thy might set  me before Thy divine judgment seat. When I am being judged, suffer not that the hand of the prince of this world should take hold of me to throw me, a sinn
e
r, into depths of Hades, but stand by me and be unto me a savior and mediator, for these bodily torments gladden Thy servants. Have mercy, O Lord, on my soul defiled through passions of this life and receive it cleansed by penitence and confession, for bl
essed art Thou unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par O come let us worship God our King. 
\par O come let us worship and fall down before  Christ our King and God.  
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King, and God. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (With Three reverences)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6177181 
\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\insrsid6177181 PSALM 120}{\insrsid6177181 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par I have lifted up mine eyes to the mountains, from whence cometh my help. My help cometh from the Lord, Who hath made heaven and   the earth. Give not Thy foot unto moving, and He not slumber that   keepeth thee. Behold, He shall not slum
ber nor shall He sleep, He that   keepeth Israel. The Lord shall keep thee: the Lord is thy shelter at thy   right hand. The sun shall not burn thee by nor the moon by night.   The Lord shall keep thee from all evil, the Lord shall guard thy soul. The Lor
d shall keep thy going and thy going out, from henceforth and for evermore.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6177181 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\insrsid6177181\charrsid6177181 PSALM 133
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Behold now, bless ye the Lord, all ye servants of the Lord. Ye that  stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God, in the nights lift up your hands unto the holies and bless the Lord. The Lord bless thee out of Sion, He that made 
heaven and the earth.
\par 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice) 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deli
ver us from the evil one. 
\par  
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181   }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 

\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6177181 READER: }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \page And these Troparia:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE 2}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Remember, O Lord, for Thou art good, Thy servants and forgive them whatsoever sins they have committed in life; for none is sinless but Thee Who art able to give repose unto them that are departed.
\par 
\par O Thou Who by the depth of Thy Wisdom dost provide all things out of love f
or mankind, and grantest unto all that which is profitable, O only Creator: Grant rest, O Lord, to the souls of Thy servants; for in Thee have they placed their hope, O our Creator and Fashioner and God.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Kontakion}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing,  but life everlasting.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Theotokion: }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 In all generations we call thee blessed, O Virgin Theotokos, for in thee the uncontainable Christ our God was pleased to be contained. Blessed are we also, having thee as mediatress; for da
y and night pleadest thou for us, and the scepters of kingdoms are strengthened by thine intercessions. Wherefore in hymns we cry unto thee; Rejoice! O thou who art full of grace, the Lord is with thee.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Lord, have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Twelve times. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And this Prayer:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181    
\par 
\par Remember, O Lord, our fathers and brethren who fell asleep in the hope of resurrection unto life eternal, and all those who ended this life in piety and faith, and pardon them every transgression which they have willfully or unwillingly, in word or deed
 or thought committed, and settle them in a place of light, a place of refreshment, a place of repose, wherefrom every sickness, sorrow and sighing are banished, and wherein from eternity the light of Thy countenance shineth and gladdeneth all Thy saints.
 
Grant unto them and unto us Thy kingdom, and participation in Thine ineffable blessings, and the enjoyment of Thine endless and blessed life. For Thou art the life, and the resurrection, and the repose of Thy departed servants, O Christ our God, and to Th
ee we send up glory, with Thine unoriginate Father, and Thy most holy and good and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.    
\par 
\par Most glorious, Ever-Virgin, Mother of Christ God, present our prayer to thy Son and our God, that through thee He may save our souls.
\par 
\par My hope is the Father, my refuge is the Son, my protection is the Holy Spirit; O Holy Trinity, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And these Troparia: 
\par 
\par SIXTH TONE:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par  
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us; / for at a loss for any defense, / this prayer do we sinners offer unto Thee as Master; // have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 
\par Lord, have mercy on us; / for we have hoped in Thee, be not angry with us greatly,  / neither remember our iniquities; / but look upon us now as Thou art compassionate,  / and deliver us from our enemies, / for Thou art our God, and we, Thy people, // all
 are the works of Thy hands, and we call upon Thy name.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par The door of compassion open unto us, O blessed Theotokos, / for, hoping in thee, let us not perish; / through thee may we be delivered from adversities, // for thou art the salvation of the Christian race.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Have mercy on us, O God, according to Thy great mercy, we pray Thee, hearken and have mercy.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Again we pray that this sacred monastery (or th
is city). and every monastery, city, town, and every country may be preserved from famine, pestilence, earthquake, flood, fire, the sword, the invasion of aliens, and civil war; that our good and man-loving God may be gracious and favorable, that He may t
urn away all the wrath stirred up against us,  and deliver us from His righteousness  which hangeth over us, and have mercy on us. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Forty times)
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Hearken unto us, O God our Savior, Thou hope of all the ends of the earth 
and of them that be far off at sea; and be merciful, be merciful, O Master, regarding our sins, and have mercy on us; for a merciful God art Thou; and the Lover of  mankind, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy
 Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Amen}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 .
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Glory to Thee, O Christ God, our hope, glory to Thee.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. Lord, have mercy, . Lord, have mercy, Lord, have mercy}{
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 . }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Father}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (master)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 , }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 bless.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181     
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 May Christ our true God, through the intercessions of His most pure Mother, of our holy and God-bearing father(s)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{
\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 N.(N)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 and all the saints, have mercy on us and save us, for He is good and the Lover of mankind.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then the priest maketh a bow (or a prostration) to the bishop/superior and to the brethren (sisters), saying: 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Bless, }{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (holy master)}{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181  holy fathers }{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (mothers)}{
\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181  and brethren and forgive me a sinner, all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and through all my senses. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And the brethren (sisters) (congregation) reply}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par May God forgive and have mercy on thee, holy father.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And they make a prostration depending on the typicon),asking this forgiveness:
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Bless me, holy father, and forgive all wherein I have sinned this day in deed, word, and thought, and in all my senses, and pray for me a sinner
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Through His grace may God forgive and have mercy on us all
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \page And he saith this Ectenia: 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Let us pray 
for the Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; for our lord the Very Most Reverend Metropolitan N., First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; for our lord the Most Reverend (Archbishop or Bishop N., whose diocese it is) and all our brethren in Chri
st.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Quietly, slowly, and repeatedly, until the petitions are finished 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 For the suffering Russian land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora, and for their
 salvation; for this land authorities and armed forces, and for every Christian land. 
\par 
\par For them that hate us and them that love us. 
\par 
\par For them that are kind to us and them that serve us. 
\par 
\par For them that have asked us unworthy ones to pray for them.
\par 
\par For the deliverance of the imprisoned. 
\par 
\par For our fathers and brethren that have passed on before us. 
\par 
\par For those sailing upon the sea. 
\par 
\par For those bedridden in infirmities. 
\par 
\par Let us pray for the abundance of the fruits of the earth. 
\par 
\par And for every Orthodox Christian soul. 
\par 
\par Let us bless pious kings (rulers), orthodox hierarchs, and the founders of this holy habitation.
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Our parents, and all that have passed on before us, our fathers, brethren, and the Orthodox here and everywhere laid to rest. 
\par 
\par Let us say also for ourselves.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 For the sake of the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother of }{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (the patron saint of the temple}{
\cs23\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 ), and the saints, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us. 
\par }{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\cs17\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Amen.}{\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And we venerate the holy icons and receive a blessing from the priest (superior) (bishop).
\par 
\par THE END OF THE MIDNIGHT OFFICE FOR WEEKDAYS and SATURDAYS
\par }{\cs26\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\insrsid6177181 
\par }}